column1: † Cell suppressed in accordance with CIHI’s privacy policy. Suppressed cells are included in the totals.
Regional values may not add up to provincial/territorial values due to missing regional information.
Percentages may not add up to 100 due to rounding.

Statistics Canada’s Statistical Area Classification type (SACtype) is used to define urban (SACtypes 1 to 3) and rural/remote (SACtypes 4 to 8) geographic locations based on the patient’s residential postal code.
CMG Care Level aggregates hospital care into mutually exclusive levels that reflect the degree of specialization.
CMG Provider Service Group aggregates hospital care into mutually exclusive groups based on the most responsible provider.
The provider service group “various” has been excluded from this analysis (approximately 9% of hospitalizations).

Ontario Mental Health Reporting System (OMHRS) data was not included in the calculations. Rates may be under-reported for Newfoundland and Labrador, Ontario and Manitoba, which have facilities reporting to OMHRS.

High/very high travel burden hospitalization rate and total hospitalization rate are age–sex-standardized rates per 1,000 population and are calculated using the direct method and the 2011 Canadian population as the standard population.

For information on the approach used to calculate travel burden categories, refer to the Methodology notes tab in this file and the document Travel Burden for Hospital Care in Canada — Methodology Notes.
